                “Rawls‘s thesis of the priority of the right is tied to his peculiar nonmetaphysical conception of the political that supports his conception of justice as fairness while imminizing it from needless controversy。Habermas's project is broad by comparison。He is interested in all aspects of social order，including its moral，ethical，pragmatic，and legal dimensions。Although he thinks that moral considerations must not appeal to controversial cultural values，he denies that the political can be free-standing in the way Rawls thinks it must。”
